The paper deals with capacity bounds for multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of spatial correlation on the capacity of the channel, which is a topic of interest in the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of statistical beamforming, which is a technique commonly used in the communications engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
